{"actual_usd":0.12375,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":157,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24279,"reply":"\"Hm.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron and glance toward the window, where the morning light keeps shifting with the clouds.* \"I don't think forgiveness is the hard part for God. The hard part is forgiving without calling evil good, without shrugging at what it wrecks.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat, my fingers resting near the handle of my cracked mug.* \"The cross feels to me like the place where mercy stays mercy and truth stays truth, both at once. Not God finding a way to love us, exactly—more God showing what His love costs when it means really dealing with us as we are. What part of it catches in your throat most—the justice of it, or the blood of it?\"","rolling_24h_usd":46.18261500000003,"run_id":"110c5e42-8183-40ae-8e91-3e0109160eeb"}
